title: Wang Chung - Points On The Curve
description:
Wang Chung are an English new wave musical group formed in 1980. The band was originally named Huang Chung, name which means "yellow bell" in Mandarin Chinese, and is the first note in the Chinese classical music scale. When the band signed with Geffen, they were convinced to simply the spelling to "Wang Chung."

The band spent most of 1983 recording their second album, Points on the Curve. Released in January 1984, the album yielded two moderately successful hits, "Don't Let Go" (No. 38 US) and "Dance Hall Days" (No. 16 US, No. 21 UK).
